\layout Title

The Mandelbrot Set as a Modular Form
\layout Author

Linas Vepstas <linas@linas.org>
\layout Date

2 January 2005 (revised 15 May 2005)
\layout Abstract

An exploration of the interior or the Mandelbrot Set and the appearance
 of functions appearing to be modular forms.
 This provides yet another example of the close interconnection between
 the structure of the Modular Group SL(2,Z) and fractals.
 The relationship is demonstrated computationally and visually, and not
 from first principles; visually, the interior closely resembles the Weierstrass
 elliptic invariant 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{2}$
\end_inset 

.
 The construction is based on averaging together iterated values with a
 spectral-type summation, and then analyzing the asymptotic behavior of
 the sum.
 Leading divergence are easy to explain and remove; the remaining finite
 parts appear to have modular symmetry.
\layout Abstract

This is a work in progress.
 A final conclusion and analysis has not been reached.
