Finite Terms
\layout Standard

Let us now turn to the finite remainders.
 By subtracting away the divergent pieces, we are essentially subtracting
 away the contribution of the asymptotic limit cycle.
 The remaining finite parts indicate how the asymptotic behavior is approached.
 If the finite part is large, this indicates that the iteration took a long
 time to approach the asymptotic limit.
 If the finite part is small, then the series converged to its limit cycle
 quickly.
 The figure 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{cap:Rate-of-Convergence}

